listing.name: Custom Fields
listing.description:
Custom fields.

Customize cards for the way you work.

The Custom Fields Power-Up enables you to add more info to your Trello cards that's specific to the way you get things done.

- **Custom text fields** – Add a space to enter names, email addresses, or other information that’s crucial for your cards to have.
- **Numbers** – Enable your cards to show story points, number of guests, order numbers, or any other number.
- **Checkbox** – Need to know when something is approved or if there are special considerations? Add a checkbox.
- **Dates** – Milestones, checkpoints, order dates—make sure crucial dates are shown on your cards.
- **Dropdown lists** – When you need to select from multiple options like status or SKUs, a dropdown is your best bet.

The info you add to your cards with Custom Fields will show up on the front of your card, making it easy to get at-a-glance info on your board. You can export Custom Field data in JSON and CSV formats. *Note: CSV exports are only available for Business Class and Enterprise Workspaces.*

![screenshot](https://card-fields.trello.services/images/custom-fields-1.jpg)\n![screenshot](https://card-fields.trello.services/images/custom-fields-2.jpg)\n![screenshot](https://card-fields.trello.services/images/custom-fields-3.jpg)
listing.overview: Add custom fields like text, numbers, checkboxes, dates, and dropdown lists to cards.

old.desc:
**ASSETS**

**Reference**
Lihat Instagram Deka Insights & McKinsey Co 

https://instagram.com/dekainsight?igshid=183zofaelzjaw

https://instagram.com/mckinseyco?igshid=3wzl8m3khccw

**Type:**
IG Feed + Story (JPEG)

**Brief**
- Bikin social media posts yg informative, targeted untuk semua org yg mau tau lebih tentang Product development journey saat pandemic ini. 
- Layout & design minta super professional, clean, consulting style, extremely premium, corporate feel.

----------

**Content**

Slide 1:

Product Development in Pandemic

80% of product developers are forced to delay their product development, but you still can be the 20%!

Slide 2:

What is happening right now?

As the government tries to prevent contact between people, your company may experience a decline in sales, especially if your business is vulnerable to COVID-19. 

These industries are most impacted by COVID-19: Hospitality, Travel, Restaurant, Manufacturing, and Construction. 

Slide 3:

Take This Opportunity to Turn Digital!

If there is a possibility to turn your business into digital, then this is the most perfect time to do so. 
If you sell a physical product, you can use delivery services like Gojek or Grab to proactively reach your customers. 

If the problem lies in the inability to do direct promotion, then you can start diving into digital marketing. 

Slide 4:

Harvard Business Review revealed how these big brands manage to overcome this pandemic era. 

- Spotify
As many companies cut up their budget for advertisement, Spotify should find other ways for monetization. 
They realized how artists upload more than 150,000 podcasts/month and use this opportunity to offer exclusive podcast contents for the users. 

- Unilever
One of the biggest FMCG brands in the world is also affected by the pandemic. While demand for skin care and other products has fallen, they prioritize packaged food, surface cleaners, and personal hygiene products that are high on demand. 
While many businesses see pandemic as a major challenge, you can turn it into your advantages or even strive to catch up with the big brand. 

Slide 5:

What do you think? Is this pandemic a disaster or it turns out to be a great opportunity?

Share your story in the column section!

listing.name: Slack
listing.description:
Turn Slack into a productivity powerhouse with the Slack Power-Up for Trello. No matter where your team is working, the Slack Power-Up for Trello makes it simple to keep your communication and collaboration apps connected so that no brilliant ideas or important tasks fall through the cracks.

- Share information with your team or get feedback on a project by sending Trello cards to Slack channels or direct messages.
- Setup configurable alerts to automatically notify Slack channels for activity in Trello at the board, list, and card level.
- Get reminders for cards when you need them in Slack, or set reminders for another teammate, so that no important tasks are ever forgotten.
- Turn brainstorms in Slack into actionable items in Trello by attaching Slack conversation to cards.
- Bring even more functionality to the Slack Power-Up with the [Trello for Slack app](https://trello.com/platforms/slack).

**ASSETS**
https://www.dropbox.com/home/Design%20Source%20Files/Dunia%20Fengshui/DF%20Logo

**Reference**
https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1G2E3h06G-IrhBX0JCUsYWZESR9UOjHKC?usp=sharing

**Type:**
IG Feed + Story (JPEG)

**Brief**
- Audience should feel very calm yet mengkuatan mreka ketika mreka selesai baca.

*Hint: Pake foto2 alami atau apapun yg bs tenangkan jiwa manusia :)

----------

**Content**
Slide 1:
Memaafkan kesalahan diri sendiri

Slide 2:
Setiap orang pasti pernah membuat kesalahan. Mungkin ada saat dimana kita merasa telah melakukan kesalahan yang begitu fatal. Sehingga kita merasa patut menyalahkan diri sendiri.

Slide 3:
Sesaat setelah kita melakukan kesalahan, biasanya kita akan merasa begitu bersalah.

Slide 4:
Perasaan bersalah memberikan informasi kepada diri kita bahwa ada sesuatu yang bertentangan dengan nilai dan kepercayaan yang kita pegang.

Slide 5:
Saat perasaan bersalah hadir dalam diri, akui perasaan tersebut. Dengan begitu, kita dapat merefleksikan diri dan kembali memperbaiki diri untuk menjadi pribadi yang lebih baik.

Slide 6:
Kesalahan yang kita buat mungkin juga mempengaruhi kondisi orang lain. Sampaikan permintaan maaf yang tulus kepada orang tersebut adalah cara yang bijak untuk dapat memperbaiki kesalahan.

Slide 7:
Jika terkadang kita masih merasakan perasaan bersalah, menulis permintaan maaf kepada diri sendiri dapat menjadi solusi untuk mengekspresikan seluruh beban dalam pikiran kita.

Slide 8:
Tidak hanya baik untuk mengekspresikan emosi kita, menuliskan permintaan maaf untuk diri sendiri dalam buku jurnal juga terbebas dari penilaian orang lain.

Slide 9:
Saat kita sudah terlanjur membuat kesalahan, percayalah kita juga berhak untuk memperbaiki diri dan menerima kesempatan kedua.

Slide 10:
Bagaimana cara sobat mengekspresikan perasaan bersalah yang mungkin pernah menghampiri?

**Type:**
IG Feed + Story (JPEG)

**Brief**
- Bikin social media posts yg informative, targeted untuk semua org yg mau tau lebih tentang Product development journey saat pandemic ini. 
- Layout & design minta super professional, clean, consulting style, extremely premium, corporate feel.

----------

**Content**

Slide 1:

Product Development in Pandemic

80% of product developers are forced to delay their product development, but you still can be the 20%!

Slide 2:

What is happening right now?

As the government tries to prevent contact between people, your company may experience a decline in sales, especially if your business is vulnerable to COVID-19. 

These industries are most impacted by COVID-19: Hospitality, Travel, Restaurant, Manufacturing, and Construction. 

Slide 3:

Take This Opportunity to Turn Digital!

If there is a possibility to turn your business into digital, then this is the most perfect time to do so. 
If you sell a physical product, you can use delivery services like Gojek or Grab to proactively reach your customers. 

If the problem lies in the inability to do direct promotion, then you can start diving into digital marketing. 

Slide 4:

Harvard Business Review revealed how these big brands manage to overcome this pandemic era. 

- Spotify
As many companies cut up their budget for advertisement, Spotify should find other ways for monetisation. 
They realised how artists upload more than 150,000 podcasts/month and use this opportunity to offer exclusive podcast contents for the users. 

- Unilever
One of the biggest FMCG brands in the world is also affected by the pandemic. While demand for skin care and other products has fallen, they prioritize packaged food, surface cleaners, and personal hygiene products that are high on demand. 
While many businesses see pandemic as a major challenge, you can turn it into your advantages or even strive to catch up with the big brand. 

Slide 5:

What do you think? Is this pandemic a disaster or it turns out to be a great opportunity?

Share your story in the column section!
